documentation.text:
A Submit corresponds to a proposal of Paper so we use the Paper's IPFS hash,
 which is represented by a string, to represent it.
 Each Submit triggers a review process. Each reviewers can add a Review to a Submit.*

Add a submit to "userToSubmits" if it doesn't exists.
 @param _ipfsHash Hash of the submitted file.*

attributes.text:
A Submit corresponds to a proposal of Paper so we use the Paper's IPFS hash,
 which is represented by a string, to represent it.
 Each Submit triggers a review process. Each reviewers can add a Review to a Submit.*

Add a submit to "userToSubmits" if it doesn't exists.
 @param _ipfsHash Hash of the submitted file.*

attributes.type: struct Reviews.Review storage ref[] storage ref
mapping(uint256 => struct Reviews.Review storage ref[] storage ref)

params._requests: List of the requests asked by the reviewer. The front will ask the reviewer the status of its review, and right after it will ask if he wants to add ChangeRequests. The reviewer will create _requests array the front which will call 'createChangeRequest'*

params._status: What the reviewers think should happen next to the submit.*

params._comment: What the reviewers think is not okay or wants changed
params._line: The line concerned by the comment (-1 if it's for the whole paper) Due to the length of a call to a contract, I think it would be best if the front can create the changeRequests by itself.*
params._page: The page concerned by the comment (-1 if it's for the whole paper)

params._status: what the reviewers think should happen next (accept, reject, change).*

addChangeRequestToReview(uint256,(string.notice: Add a list of requests to a newly created review.

addReview(string,uint8).notice: Add a new review to a submit and returns the review's id;

createChangeRequest(string,int256,int256.notice: Helper function which simply returns a ChangeRequest.

createReview(uint8).notice: Create a review and returns it's id so the front can possibly add ChangeRequests

newSubmit(string).notice: Add a submit to "userToSubmits" if it doesn't exists.

userdoc.notice: A Submit corresponds to a proposal of Paper so we use the Paper's IPFS hash, which is represented by a string, to represent it. Each Submit triggers a review process. Each reviewers can add a Review to a Submit.*
